J&uuml;rgen Klopp insists Liverpool will be in no rush to hand Virgil van Dijk his debut for the club after the centre-back finalised his transfer from Southampton on New Year&rsquo;s Day. (@LFC)<br />
<br />
Klopp on potential Van Dijk debut: &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t know. We made a few tests that make sense only for him and for us, to see where he stands. That&rsquo;s all. There is no rush.&quot;

Jurgen Klopp declared himself uninterested with the latest instalment of the Philippe Coutinho transfer saga after Liverpool began 2018 with a big three points at Burnley. (@neiljonesecho)<br />
<br />
Klopp on Nike's Coutinho comments: &ldquo;I heard about it, I can't tell you about it though because for different reasons I couldn&rsquo;t be less interested in anything in the world. But somebody told me and I thought 'wow! Top story!'&rdquo;

Van Dijk on his price tag: &quot;Obviously there is a lot of money being paid, but I can't do anything about that money, I can't do anything about the price - nobody can.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Van Dijk on his price tag: &quot;It's only the market. The only thing I can do is just work hard, do the good things and be 100 percent every day. That's what I definitely want to do - and I am going to do.&rdquo;

